    "description":  "Guidance for those who wish to apply for an Economic Advisers vacancy.",
    "details":  {
                    "attachments":  [

                                    ],
                    "body":  "\u003cdiv class=\"govspeak\"\u003e\u003ch2 id=\"grade-7-economic-advisers\"\u003eGrade 7 Economic Advisers\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e£45k+\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003ePermanent/fixed term for three years with possibility of permanency\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eJoin us and use your economic skills to influence policy and transform lives.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis scheme has now closed.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3 id=\"transforming-lives\"\u003eTransforming Lives\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis is a high-profile opportunity to join the Government Economic Service and use your skills and knowledge as a professional economist to improve the lives of millions, working to formulate, implement, and evaluate government policy across a range of areas.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3 id=\"high-profile\"\u003eHigh Profile\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWherever you join the GES, you’ll be delivering rigorous economic analysis to advise ministers and senior officials, ensuring that policy is informed by the strongest possible analytical underpinnings. Strengthening the evidence base and evaluating the costs and benefits of different policy options will also likely form part of your remit.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3 id=\"variety-of-roles\"\u003eVariety of Roles\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWe are looking for professional economists to join us and work in more than 12 Departments across a range of locations, including:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003eDepartment for Exiting the EU\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003eDepartment for International Development\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003eDepartment for International Trade\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003eDepartment for Environment, Food \u0026amp; Rural Affairs\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003eOffice for National Statistics\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003eScottish Government\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAdditional posts in other government departments may become available before the closing date and further details of all posts are available on our website www.ges.gov.uk.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3 id=\"the-person\"\u003eThe Person\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eReady for far-reaching influence, you will have a proven track record as a professional economist supported by a 2:1 degree and/or MSc in economics. It’s possible you’re currently working in the third sector or an Arms Length Body (ALB), a consultancy, or a research organisation so you’ll have some expertise in the areas we work in. You’ll definitely have strong project management skills. Your flair for analysing a large amount of data, making effective decisions, and developing and managing others will be matched by sound understanding of economic theory. Your talent for communicating your findings to a wide range of audiences, including very senior stakeholders, through briefings and advice will make you stand out.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3 id=\"a-great-package\"\u003eA Great Package\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWe want our people to have a good work life balance so we offer a family-friendly environment, flexible working, a commitment to continuous learning and development and an attractive pension scheme. Civil Service nationality rules allow us to accept only applications from UK nationals, Commonwealth citizens or European Economic Area and Swiss Nationals.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAll applications should be sent to \u003ca href=\"mailto:GESRRecruitment@HMTreasury.gsi.gov.uk\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eGESRRecruitment@HMTreasury.gsi.gov.uk\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe Civil Service is an Equal Opportunities employer and aims to reflect the diversity of British society. All applications are treated on merit.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003c/div\u003e",
